================================================================
 pipnode-zigbee-plugin -- TODO
================================================================

Plain text only; no markdown. Level-0 items are numbered
sequentially; their sub-items are bulleted, not numbered.


----------------------------------------------------------------
 Adopt pipnode's enhanced error-reporting / logging facilities
 (PLUGINS section 12)
----------------------------------------------------------------

The host now offers a three-channel failure-reporting contract
that nodes are expected to use (all GTK-free, available headless):

  - Downstream: emit a PnMessage with success=FALSE + a
    human-readable output.
  - Visual: pn_node_set_has_error (node, TRUE/FALSE)
    (pn-node.h:708); the host paints the red body + warning glyph
    itself. PLUGINS section 12 explicitly forbids hand-rolling
    that swap via pn_node_set_color / pn_node_set_icon.
  - Diagnostics log: pn_node_log() /
    pn_node_log_info|warning|error() (pn-node.h:726-754) instead
    of stdout/stderr or silent drops.

Audit (2026-05-29): Channels 2 and 3 are now both done (items 1
and 2 below). pn-zigbee-remote.c (pn_node_log_info per press,
:247) is no longer the only node that logs.

1. Channel 2 -- replace the hand-rolled red+glyph swap with
   pn_node_set_has_error: DONE (2026-05-29).
   - DONE. The three zigbee swaps (pn-zigbee-switch.c,
     pn-zigbee-relay-status.c, pn-zigbee-relay-command.c) likewise
     keep magenta + toggle glyph and toggle has_error while
     unconfigured (empty friendly-name). Decision: "unconfigured"
     does count as a node-error state -- has_error is purely visual
     in the host (no error aggregation / downstream side effect),
     so the outcome is the identical red ❗ while complying with
     section 12's ban on hand-rolled swaps. (pn-zigbee-remote.c
     needs no migration: its friendly-name is an optional filter,
     not a mandatory config, so it has no unconfigured-error state.)

2. Channel 3 -- adopt pn_node_log_* for diagnostics: DONE
   (2026-05-29).
   Guiding rule applied: log a drop only where it is a genuine
   diagnostic of bounded frequency. Drops on the broker-traffic
   read path are deliberately left silent -- topic_matches_zigbee_
   state matches the bare device topic zigbee2mqtt/<name>, on which
   Z2M republishes every attribute (state, brightness, linkquality,
   ...), so an absent "state" member is the routine case and would
   flood the per-node log ring on every update.
   - DONE. src/pn-zigbee-source.c rebuild_device_cache -- a WARNING
     when the bridge/devices payload is not a JSON array (and the
     prior cache is now kept untouched on that path); plus one
     aggregated WARNING ("skipped N entries with no usable
     friendly_name") instead of per-element spam.
   - DONE. src/pn-zigbee-switch.c -- WARNING on the unconfigured
     outbound fallback (user-toggle bounded); INFO on a present-but-
     non-binary inbound state (e.g. "TOGGLE"). The state==NULL /
     wrong-topic / unconfigured *read* drops stay silent (see rule).
   - DONE. src/pn-zigbee-relay-status.c -- INFO on a present-but-
     non-binary inbound state, mirroring the switch. read-path
     filtering drops stay silent.
   - DONE. src/pn-zigbee-relay-command.c -- WARNING when a
     configured node gets an input with no usable numeric value
     (upstream-emit bounded). The unconfigured drop stays silent
     (the red error visual already flags it, and it would repeat on
     every upstream emit).


----------------------------------------------------------------
 PnZigbeeSwitch reports class_name "Switch" instead of
 "Zigbee Switch"
----------------------------------------------------------------

3. pn-zigbee-switch.c:405 pins node_class->class_name = "Zigbee
   Switch", but pn_node_get_class_name() on an instance returns
   "Switch". The PnSwitch base seeds a *per-instance* class-name
   label (the legacy override path), and the instance value shadows
   the subclass's class-level value. The other nodes derive from
   PnNode directly and are unaffected (they report their correct
   class_name). Likely surfaced by commit 5fd9ad9, which dropped
   the deprecated pn_node_set_class_name() calls from node init.
   - Decide whether the palette/inspector should show "Zigbee
     Switch" (it should). If so, re-assert the per-instance label
     in pn_zigbee_switch_init (the supported setter), or have the
     host stop seeding an instance-level override from PnSwitch.
     Caught by tests/test-zigbee-switch.c (which currently does
     not assert class_name for this reason).
   - Update (2026-05-29): the host getter was already fixed for
     this -- pipnode commit 97acd76 made pn_node_get_class_name()
     fall back to the class-level PnNodeClass.class_name when there
     is no per-instance override (lib/pn-node.c:889-898), and
     deprecated pn_node_set_class_name() for plugin _init() use.
     That alone does NOT fix us, though: PnSwitch's own
     pn_switch_init still seeds a per-instance "Switch"
     (lib/pn-switch.c:462) -- 97acd76 cleaned up pn_mqtt_init but
     left pn-switch.c -- so the getter finds that non-empty
     per-instance value and never reaches the new class-level
     fallback. Decided fix: drop the pn_node_set_class_name (node,
     "Switch") line at pn-switch.c:462 in pipnode (mirroring the
     pn_mqtt_init cleanup); then PnZigbeeSwitch inherits "Zigbee
     Switch" for free. To be done in pipnode later; once landed,
     enable the class_name assertion in tests/test-zigbee-switch.c.


----------------------------------------------------------------
 Code-review findings (2026-05-29)
----------------------------------------------------------------

Found by a multi-agent review of the full source. No
memory-safety or registration bugs were found; ownership of
JsonNode / GString / PnMessage is correct throughout. The items
below are behavioral / contract issues.

4. success flag: switch's configured vs unconfigured paths
   disagree (minor).
   data.success=FALSE is the section-12 downstream failure signal
   -- i.e. "did the node do its job". These nodes only build and
   emit a message (a downstream PnMqttSink does any actual
   publishing; nothing touches hardware), so no property
   combination can stop them emitting and success = TRUE is correct
   by design. The configured paths (pn-zigbee-switch.c:156,
   pn-zigbee-relay-command.c:190, pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:210) get
   this right. The lone wrinkle: the base PnSwitch builder
   overloads success to carry the latch state (success = on,
   ../pipnode/.../pn-switch.c:124). That leaks into the Zigbee
   switch *only* on the unconfigured fallback path
   (pn-zigbee-switch.c:133-134), so within one node success means
   "always true" when configured but "is-on" when not.
   - Optionally make the unconfigured fallback also stamp
     success = TRUE for self-consistency. Low priority -- the
     unconfigured case is a misconfiguration the warning visual
     already flags, and success is correct on the path that
     matters.

5. PnZigbeeSource: malformed/empty bridge/devices is dropped and
   leaves a stale cache.
   src/pn-zigbee-source.c:731-737, :592-596 -- a garbage or
   momentarily-[] inventory publish is swallowed (default
   filter_bridge_devices=TRUE), the device cache is not refreshed,
   and nothing is logged; the node then runs on stale device info
   invisibly. (Deeper than the section-12 logging item for :590.)
   - Log a warning on the not-an-array / empty case, and consider
     keeping the previous cache when the new array is empty.

6. Boolean Z2M state is silently dropped (switch & relay nodes).
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-command.c:116-122,
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:146, src/pn-zigbee-switch.c:220 --
    value/state readers accept only string / int64 / double, so Z2M
    endpoints that express "state": true as a JSON boolean are
    ignored. Consistent across the three, so a gap rather than a
    divergence.
    - Optionally accept G_TYPE_BOOLEAN for state / value.

7. PnZigbeeRelayStatus leaves the live device state topic on its
    emitted message.
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:204-218 -- never calls
    pn_message_set_topic, unlike relay-command which rewrites it
    (:166-168). Wiring relay-status to an MQTT Sink that republishes
    on the inbound topic would echo onto the device's state topic.
    Latent foot-gun.
    - Clear the topic on the emitted message, or document why it's
      left intact.

8. Test-coverage gaps (not bugs).
    - PnZigbeeSource has zero unit tests -- its Z2M filter/inject
      logic (the most complex code in the plugin) is uncovered
      because constructing it auto-connects libmosquitto
      off-thread. Worth an integration test against a throwaway
      broker.
